<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Turc</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2003<br />
	Location: Warner Robins, GA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I've noticed the pattern for a while, but I'm just now trying to get an explanation.  I know DoT aggro is broken, but I am wondering how it is broken.  I'm not sure if any of you know either.<br />
<br />
This is how I handle a normal encounter in BoT:  Malos on incoming, send in Dogdog (with taunt off), slow as soon as I can, then usually Bane soon after that.  Everything is ok until about tick #2 or 3 of Bane.  Then the mob comes running for me.  <br />
I understand that is going to happen, and I am not worried about a slowed BoT mob hitting me.<br />
<br />
My question is, why does it take two or three ticks for me to get aggro?  I could cast a DD 3 or 4 times in a row and not get aggro.  So is it because that the curse counters get added every tick?  Bane adds 24 curse counters and is 5 ticks long (normally).  So by the end of the DoT, is 120 curse counters on the mob?</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=596872">  <b><font color="cc6600">Turc</b> (Retired: 12/17/04)</font></a> </font</div>
	
	
