<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Drinnar</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Luminary<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2002<br />
	Location: Terris-Thule
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Dots generate extreme aggro when they land because of the counters associated with them, poison are particularly bad.  Then every tick when you do some measly amount of damage they generate even more aggro.  Counters do not get readded every tick, which can be tested by doting yourself and curing it, but there's something definately broken with dots and the devs haven't done anything about it in 5 years<br />
<br />
I'm guessing they run on a 1:1 damage to aggro ratio, but the formulas for aggro generation have never been made public so no one really knows.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
