	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I too think people give counters too much weight. Every spell in fact adds counters of some type(if you look up dispells you can clearly see how many counters they dispell).<br />
Spells have a certain aggro value attached, regardless of the counters and when you refer to a Malos to Tash comparison as proof, I can simply tell you to compare Cripple to Tash. Cripple, as we all know, doesn't add any poison counters, yet it's at least as much aggro.<br />
<br />
From the beginning poison DoTs have been coded to generate huge aggro and every new spell that they add of the line is basically copied over first, before they change a few numbers like Damage/tick etc.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Shaman ?!</div>
	
	
