<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Landragoran Heronwing</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	GNOMERCY!<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2000<br />
	Location: back to cally to cally
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>it's all in the counters.  Poison counters = MASSIVE UNCONTROLLED aggro.  Poison counters are clearly broken, as the aggro associated with them is over the top.<br />
Disease counters used to generate mad aggro too, however, when Sony decided to make Slow curable, and added disease counters, all slow spells were for a few months "broken" as in if you slowed a mob you would get holy gawd aggro in a way you should not.  They tried this and that and finally settled on just removing all aggro associated with disease counters.  That worked to fix slow aggro, and had the positive affect of making disease DoTs be very little aggro.  Or at least, no more aggro than their DPS warranted. <br />
<br />
Curse counters haven't been parsed for aggro yet, so it's hard to say.  However, it does appear that they lie somewhere between disease counters and poison counters for aggro.  Much less than poison tho, since in my own experiments I have found that Bane generates less aggro than Blood of Saryrn, when applied at the same time in the same situation with the same tank.  Thus PR counters >> curse counters for aggro.  <br />
And you have to keep in mind that Bane does about a fourth more damage than BoS.  So clearly curse counters generate much less aggro than poison counters.  <br />
<br />
If they removed the poison counters from Tash line of Enchanter spells, the Enchies would just love it.  Tash would become a negligible aggro spell, just like Malo line is today.  <br />
<br />
Point is, what is currently broken is poison counter aggro.  Fix that and our problems largely go away. <br />
<br />
I attribute Bane aggro to this: Slow aggro plus Bane DPS plus smallish tank aggro generation due to inferior skills/equipment/playstyle.</p>
	
	
	
