	<!-- message -->
	<p>Trust me, counters aren't the real source of the aggro associated with those spells. There are countless spells with huge aggro which have no poison counters whatsoever.<br />
<br />
Further proof is that a resisted Blood is huge aggro, which in theory it should not if it was about the counters, because counters aren't even applied in case of a resist. I am pretty sure the aggro from Tash was warranted by the fast cast time and it being unresistable from level 1(the only unresistable spell for a long time).<br />
<br />
This doesn't mean that poison DoTs are not higher aggro than our Curse ones. They definitely ARE. But the problem lies more in the coding than in the counters. The code for spells like Blood of Saryrn is more than 5 years old.</p>
	
	
	
