	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>veeshanMurtak</b><br /><i>I can not pull aggro off my guild's tanks with resisted banes and bloods. I can pull aggro if I land them and just refresh them, casting perhaps 1/5 as much DoTs overall.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Which shows that there is an inherent problem with how the hate/damage ratio for DoTs is calculated. Resisted Bloods doesn't do any damage, thus the hate is overall lower. <br />
A resisted Blood, however, generates more aggro than a resisted Bane(none of the spells will place counters on the NPC) and I suspect every point of damage from a DoT to generate X amount of aggro, regardless of the counters.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />As to non-counter spells generating aggro: As others have already pointed out AC debuffs seem to be huge too.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>As I said before, *all* spells that leave an icon on a mob have "counters". Some are just not cureable, yet different non-cureable spells will have different counters, which seem to have no relation to the aggro they generate, though.<br />
<br />
I have no proof, but I highly suspect that hate attached to spells is based on the type of spell. Spells that the Devs considered very powerful back then(Slows, Tash, AC debuff) generate a lot of aggro. <br />
<br />
The fact, that Malo(s) generates very low aggro, is a result of them being an upgrade of the Malaise line(which was very resistable). They must have merely changed the entry Resist: Magic to Resist: Unresistable without changing the entry for Hate(1-10):1(hypothetical field here).<br />
<br />
Keep in mind that these speculations are just based on observations.</p>
	
	
	
