<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Juujuu</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Heyokah<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 1999<br />
	Location: Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Removing the poison counters isn't the fix.<br />
Removing the aggro from the poison counters is the fix, just like they did with disease dots long ago.<br />
The counters with disease caused massive damage.<br />
Disease counter aggro being "nerfed" was one of the main reasons SKs now have pure taunt spells.<br />
They came to rely on spells like <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=340&amp;source=Live" target="_blank">disease cloud</a>  to pull aggro, even through it was a level 9 spell for them doing a massive 5 damage + 1 per tick and only giving 1 disease counter.<br />
They would just cast disease cloud on a mob, and pull aggro almost immediately.<br />
And if they didn't, the recast time was super fast such that they could chain cast it until they got aggro from this spell, and it was essentially no mana cost (well, it's 10 mana, which doesn't count compared to spending 10-30x as much mana now for the same effect off other spells).<br />
Drop aggro from poison counters is the fix.</p>
	
	
	
