<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>jzak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>You may be able to set up a test of how much aggro each spell actually generates by using an SK and their aggro spells.  Have them cast Terror of Thule/Terris, which have fixed hate amounts, and then throw on one of your spells and see when they turn.  It would work like a Diophantine equation.<br />
<br />
a*x - b*y = 0<br />
<br />
a = amount of hate Terror of Thule/Terris gives<br />
x = number of times SK casts the spell<br />
<br />
b = amount of hate shaman spell gives<br />
y = number of times shaman casts the spell<br />
<br />
<br />
It would require a lot of values, since you're really solving to find the value of b for a particular spell.  The good news is that this equation will always have a solution.  The bad news is that you'll have to factor out a lot of stuff that might affect aggro additionally (distance from mob, ticks of damage on DoTs, etc).  It's probably easier to bug a developer to reveal the value a certain spell has.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=aa04df70cd6993f17dc6dcc6e0f2e0cf&amp;postid=262581">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=aa04df70cd6993f17dc6dcc6e0f2e0cf&amp;do=getip&postid=262581">Logged</a></div>
	
