</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Near as I've been able to figure, the damage a DoT somehow has its aggro modified by the counters to which it is applied, something like damage * counter aggro modifier = hate.  Thus, damage dealt by disease and epic have little aggro per tick because it's low or moderate damage applied to low-aggro counters, but a spell like Blood of Saryrn or Bane has HIGH damage modified by HIGH AGGRO counters.  The initial landing doesn't pull aggro, the first one or two ticks don't, but that massive hate built up by the modified "hate damage ratio" of hp of damage to hate point eventually overwhelms everything.<br />
<br />
All I really know is Slow + Cripple + Blood of Saryrn + Bane = absolutely no way in the universe you're taking aggro away from me...provided I live long enough to cast them all.<br />
<br />
They call us kings of slow.  They should call us kings of aggro instead.  If there's anything we can truly own, it's aggro.</p>
	
	
	
