	<!-- message -->
	<p>One thing that gives me the impression that poison counters are PART of the problem (obviously not all of the problem, note the evidence provided so far in this thread) is the aggro associated with tash.  <br />
<br />
Compare Howl of Tashan:<br />
Slot Description <br />
1:  Increase Poison Counter by 1 <br />
2:  Decrease Magic Resist by 48 (L61) to 50 (L64) <br />
<br />
with Malos:<br />
Slot Description <br />
2:  Decrease Cold Resist by 55 <br />
3:  Decrease Magic Resist by 55 <br />
4:  Decrease Poison Resist by 55 <br />
5:  Decrease Fire Resist by 55 <br />
<br />
Now, based on the actual debuff of the spells, and the fact that both are unresistable, One would think that Malos would be MUCH higher aggro, however in practice we know this is false.  Considering lucy is pretty good at spotting straight +hate effects on spells, that leaves you with the *1* poison counter as the difference.  Poison counters DO have a heavey aggro cost.</p>
	
	
	
