<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Kireiina</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2002<br />
	Location: Oz-land
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Speaking as a necro (ex-shaman), who basically does nothing else but DoT's things, I can assure you that the counters have a lot to do with it. It's virtually impossible to pull agro with disease spells, It's virtually impossible not to pull agro with poison spells. It doesn't specifically matter which spell you use, all spells with poison counters are high agro. Curse counters are significantly less, but still higher than counter free DoT's.<br />
<br />
Putting down relatively fast, counter free DoT's, such as funeral pyre attract very little agro. Suggesting that a DoT is otherwise considered as a series of small nukes for agro purposes. Of course a DoT with an effect, such as snare, attracts additional agro for that effect which is almost certainly applied only on landing.<br />
<br />
Just my perceptions. Proving this conclusively will be rather tedious.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
		<div class="smallfont"><a href="report.php?s=aa04df70cd6993f17dc6dcc6e0f2e0cf&amp;postid=263451">Report Post</a> | IP: <a href="postings.php?s=aa04df70cd6993f17dc6dcc6e0f2e0cf&amp;do=getip&postid=263451">Logged</a></div>
	
